%e A004137 a(7)=17: Label the 7 nodes 0,1,8,11,13,15,17 and include all edges except those from 8 to 15, from 13 to 15, from 13 to 17 and from 15 to 17. {0,1,8,11,13,15,17} is a restricted difference basis w.r.t. 17.
%e A004137 a(21)=153 because there exists a complete ruler (i.e., one that can measure every distance between 1 and 153) with marks [0,1,2,3,7,14,21,28,43,58,73,88,103,118,126,134,142,150,151,152,153] and no complete ruler of greater length with the same number of marks can be found. This ruler is of the type described by B. Wichmann and it is conjectured by _Peter Luschny_ that it is impossible to improve upon Wichmann's construction for finding optimal rulers of bigger lengths.
